I"<p>The Hisense AEH-W4A1 is a WiFi module used to give WiFi connectivity to some Hisense ACs and rebranded models (Smart Cool, Beko and others).</p>
<p>Later AC models use other WiFi modules (like AEH-W4B1 and AEH-W4E1) that are not compatible or otherwise tested with this integration.</p>
<p>It is highly recommended not to use one of the official smartphone applications and this integration at the same time, to avoid problems related to command collision.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>To integrate one or more Hisense AEH-W4A1 controlled ACs with Home Assistant, use the Configuration/Integrations or add the following section to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Automatic discovery
hisense_aehw4a1:
</code></pre>
<p>Alternately, devices that are not discoverable can be statically configured.
The use of static configuration disables automatic discovery.</p>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='ip_address' href='#ip_address'></a> ip_address</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='list'>list</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>One or more static IP addresses</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
<h2>Full configuration example</h2>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Static configured devices
hisense_aehw4a1:
  ip_address:
  - 192.168.5.10
  - 192.168.5.20
</code></pre>
